        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Hiroya Nozaki",
          "email": "nozaki.hiroya@jp.fujitsu.com",
          "date": "2015-05-26 06:49:24.000000000",
          "tz": 540
        },
        "subject": "LU-6643 llite: write hang up with small max_cached_mb",
        "message": "LU-6643 llite: write hang up with small max_cached_mb\n\nRunning multiple WRITEs at the same time with small_max_cached_mb\nresults in hang-up. It's because WRITEs eat up lru slots all at once\nbut no one have enough lru slots to start I/O. To make matters worse\nno one will release lru slots they've reserved until it completes I/O.\nThat's why all the WRITEs have to wait each other eternally.\n\nThis patch let the only one \"privileged\" WRITE ignore the lru\nlimitation so that it go ahead, release lru slots and next one can go.\n\nSigned-off-by: Hiroya Nozaki <nozaki.hiroya@jp.fujitsu.com>\nChange-Id: I114495c297b3b907a1701b1892dfd1c9edd6c321\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
